{
  "texts": [
    "Exceptions that deal with the identification of entire fields can be found in full waveform inversion [320], topology optimization [321], elasticity, and the heat equation [322].",
    "Inverse problemsPINNs are capable of discovering governing equations by either learning the operator N or the coefficients λ.",
    "The resulting operator is, however, not always interpretable, and in the case of identification of the coefficients, the underlying PDE is assumed.",
    "To discover interpretable operators, one can apply sparse regression approaches [323].",
    "Here, potential differential operators are assumed as an input to the non-linear operatorN x, u, ∂u ∂ x, ∂ 2 u ∂ x 2,... = 0."
  ]
}